<p>I have used <a href="https://github.com/pepperonas/FxIconics" rel="nofollow">Android-Iconics library, developed by Mike Penz</a> for my Javafx project. <br/></p>  <p>Code:</p>  <pre><code>Tab tab1 = new Tab(); FxIconicsLabel labelDefault                 = (FxIconicsLabel) new FxIconicsLabel.Builder(FxFontAwesome.Icons.faw_user)                 .size(18)                 .color(Color.web("#555555"))                 .build(); tab1.setGraphic(labelDefault); tab1.setText(" Customer"); </code></pre>  <p>CSS:</p>  <pre><code>.tab:selected {     -fx-border-color: #ddd #ddd #fff #ddd;     -fx-border-radius: 5 5 0 0;     -fx-text-fill: #555555;     -fx-font-weight: bold ; } </code></pre>  <p>I want to change the icon i.e (labelDefault) COLOR using css, when tab is selected.</p>